<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-247-084 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 846 071</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  Jan 7 1991 v8 n1 p88(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Batch Console maintains login scripts: Knozall Systems tool canbuild interactive batch files, customized menus. (Software Review)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Provine, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Batch Console, $295 per server from Knozall Systems, is an easy toinstall and use Netware administrator's tool designed to simplifyand enhance the job of editing login scripts and login batchfiles.andP;  While not a 'killer app', Batch Console will be fullyappreciated by any network administrator who has ever been facedwith the task of tuning an entire department's login scripts toaccommodate a new piece of hardware.andP;  In addition to the mainscript editor, Batch Console comprises a utility to constructbatch file menus using DOS error-level statements and one toprompt the user for input during batch file execution, a mappingutility, and one that controls interaction with SEND and BROADCASTmessages.andP;  The package's batch file utilities facilitate buildingcustomized end-user menus.andP;  A nice feature of the mapping utilityis that it shows the drive letters available in addition to thedrives already mapped.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Knozall Systems x (Products).andO;Product:   Batch Console (Utility program).andO;Topic:     EvaluationBatch ProcessingUtility Programs.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>